あるがまま = あるがまま = arugamama = as things are, accepting reality as it is.
人生をあるがままに生きる。 = じんせいを あるがままに いきる = jinsei o arugamama ni ikiru = Live life as it is.
一期一会 = いちごいちえ = ichigo ichie = once-in-a-lifetime encounter - Cherishing each moment as unique.
一期一会の出会いを大切に。 = いちごいちえの であいを たいせつに = ichigo ichie no deai o taisetsu ni = Treasure every once-in-a-lifetime meeting.
はんこ = はんこ = hanko = hanko stamp, personal seal - Japanese name stamp used instead of signature.
書類にはんこを押した。 = しょるいにはんこを おした = shorui ni hanko o oshita = I stamped the document with my hanko.
会釈 = えしゃく = eshaku = light greeting bow (15°) - Casual bow for acquaintances.
軽く会釈して挨拶した。 = かるく えしゃくして あいさつした = karuku eshaku shite aisatsu shita = I greeted him with a light bow.
敬礼 = けいれい = keirei = respectful bow (30-40°) - Business or formal bow toward superiors.
上司に敬礼した。 = じょうしに けいれいした = jōshi ni keirei shita = I bowed respectfully to my boss.
最敬礼 = さいけいれい = saikeirei = deepest reverent bow (45°+) - For high respect or formal occasions.
社長に最敬礼をした。 = しゃちょうに さいけいれいをした = shachō ni saikeirei o shita = I gave the deepest bow to the president.
土下座 = どげざ = dogeza = dogeza (kneeling bow with forehead to ground) - Extreme bow for deep apology.
土下座して謝った。 = どげざして あやまった = dogeza shite ayamatta = I apologized on my knees with my forehead to the ground.
お宝 = おたから = otakara = treasure, valuable possession, cherished item - Often used casually for precious things.
このゲームでお宝を見つけた！ = このゲームで おたからを みつけた！ = kono gēmu de otakara o mitsuketa! = I found treasure in this game!
財宝 = ざいほう = zaihō = treasure, wealth - Valuable objects or riches.
海賊が財宝を隠した。 = かいぞくが ざいほうを かくした = kaizoku ga zaihō o kakushita = The pirates hid the treasure.
まさか = まさか = masaka = no way, impossible, you can't be serious - Expresses disbelief.
まさか本当なのか？ = まさか ほんとうなのか？ = masaka hontō na no ka? = No way, is that true?
歳月 = さいげつ = saigetsu = years, passage of time - The flow of years/time.
歳月が人を変える。 = さいげつが ひとを かえる = saigetsu ga hito o kaeru = Time changes people.
ずいぶん = ずいぶん = zuibun = very, quite, considerably, surprisingly - Indicates degree or surprise.
ずいぶん寒くなったね。 = ずいぶん さむくなったね = zuibun samuku natta ne = It’s gotten quite cold, hasn’t it?
とりあえず = とりあえず = toriaezu = for now, tentatively, first of all - Temporary measure.
とりあえずこれでいいよ。 = とりあえず これで いいよ = toriaezu kore de ii yo = This will do for now.
つまり = つまり = tsumari = in other words, basically - Used to summarize or clarify.
つまり君の言うことは間違ってるよ。 = つまり きみの いうことは まちがってるよ = tsumari kimi no iu koto wa machigatteru yo = In other words, you’re wrong.
つもり = つもり = tsumori = intention, plan, purpose - What one intends to do.
留学するつもりだ。 = りゅうがくする つもりだ = ryūgaku suru tsumori da = I intend to study abroad.
素晴らしい = すばらしい = subarashī = wonderful, amazing, excellent, superb - Strong admiration.
この景色は素晴らしい！ = このけしきは すばらしい！ = kono keshiki wa subarashī! = This view is amazing!
約束 = やくそく = yakusoku = promise, appointment, agreement - Casual promise or formal arrangement.
約束を守るのが大事だ。 = やくそくを まもるのが だいじだ = yakusoku o mamoru no ga daiji da = Keeping promises is important.
済まない = すまない = sumanai = I'm sorry (informal), excuse me - Casual apology with regret.
本当に済まない。 = ほんとうに すまない = hontō ni sumanai = I’m really sorry.
安心する = あんしんする = anshin suru = to feel relieved, to be at ease.
安心して大丈夫だよ。 = あんしんして だいじょうぶだよ = anshin shite daijōbu da yo = Don’t worry, it’s okay.
さすが = さすが = sasuga = as expected, impressive as usual - Compliment for living up to reputation.
さすがプロだね。 = さすが プロだね = sasuga puro da ne = As expected from a pro.
無理 = むり = muri = impossible, unreasonable, excessive - Beyond one’s power or “no way”.
それは無理だと思う。 = それは むりだ とおもう = sore wa muri da to omou = I think that’s impossible.
気づかない = きづかない = kizukanai = to not notice, to be unaware.
彼は自分の間違いに気づかない。 = かれは じぶんの まちがいに きづかない = kare wa jibun no machigai ni kizukanai = He doesn’t notice his own mistake.
暗黒 = あんこく = ankoku = darkness (evil/sinister), dark age - Negative or evil darkness.
暗黒の時代が続いた。 = あんこくの じだいが つづいた = ankoku no jidai ga tsuzuita = A dark age continued.
生き延びる = いきのびる = ikinobiru = to survive, to live on - Continue existing through danger.
厳しい状況でも生き延びた。 = きびしい じょうきょうでも いきのびた = kibishii jōkyō demo ikinobita = He survived even in harsh conditions.
真実 = しんじつ = shinjitsu = truth, sincerity - Facing or speaking the truth.
真実を話してくれ。 = しんじつを はなしてくれ = shinjitsu o hanashite kure = Tell me the truth.






























































